Lance Klusener after the WC of 1999: "I wanted to be there at the end. That was my drug". In my observation, David Miller stands out as the lone player for South Africa who possesses a similar resilient mentality, making him the sole mentally strong player for the team in the knockout stages since Klusener. He showed it on two occasions in the last two knockout matches of the ODI World Cups for SA. In the 2015 WC semi, facing New Zealand, when the overs were reduced due to rain, he scored 49 with a strike rate of around 272. On that day, his performance allowed South Africa to have a fighting chance against New Zealand. In the current World Cup, he managed to score 101 in an extraordinary and seemingly hopeless situation. It appears that, unlike others, he remains unaffected by both rain and the pressure of knockout situations. It's likely that he adopted this mindset from Klusener directly since he had Klusener as his coach early in his career (https://indianexpress.com/.../ive-been-fortunate-to-have.../). 
Given his current age, it's unlikely that he will be available to fight for SA in the 2027 World Cup at home. Nevertheless, whether SA discovers another player of the caliber of de Villiers, Kallis, Pollock, or Steyn, it is imperative for them to find/ develop a player with nerves of steel, similar to Klusener or Miller. This is essential for them to put up a strong fight in knockout matches or even to reach the knockout stage. He has become my favorite South African player after Klusener and de Villiers! While many players can hit sixes, nothing can match the elegance and style with which David Miller hits sixes. Thank you David Miller for the wonderful memories and wish you good luck in your future endeavors! 
 #DavidMiller #SA #CWC23

ওয়ার্ল্ড ক্রিকেটে এমন দুইটা টীম সাপোর্ট করি, যাদের সিলেক্টরস থেকে শুরু করে প্লেয়ারস সবকিছু করাপ্টেড । একই দিনে এই দুই টিমের খেলা মানে Torture on Eyes! দুই টিমের সেইম প্রবলেম । ওদের কোন ব্যাটিং ডেপথ নাই । কতগুলা Pseudo-All-Rounder, Pseudo-Finisher টিমে ঢুকে বসে থাকে উইথআউট এনি আউটপুট । স্ক্রিনশটে সাউথ আফ্রিকার '99 WC এর টীমটা দেখলেই বুঝে যাবেন, বর্তমান সাউথ আফ্রিকা এবং বাংলাদেশ কতটা পিছনে । অস্ট্রেলিয়া, ইংল্যান্ড, নিউজিল্যান্ড, ইন্ডিয়া, পাকিস্তান এদের টীম দেখলে ঈর্ষা হয়। How good their selectors/players are, and the fans of those teams should be proud of their team, and why shouldn't they be? 
Modern cricket has changed, and you should have good all-rounders to take you to the target after 5-6 wickets down! In the 1st ODI, Australia won the match from 113/7 to 225/7. And look at the current South Africa and Bangladesh teams in 1st and 2nd ODIs. If five wickets get down within 150 runs, no one can take them to a decent score/ chase the target! 
The coming World Cup in October is for Australia, England, New Zealand, India, and Pakistan! The others are only participating. It would be a tough battle between Bangladesh and South Africa as the bottom team! Cheers

The game and raffle draw moments from Mamoni's first birthday celebration that we did last week! It was fun. 
 Thank you all for joining the program and wishing our Mamoni on her first birthday. We enjoyed a lot celebrating with you all. 
 By the way, I would like to thank some fantastic people living around us, because of them we could able to think of arranging this large-scaled program. They were excited to celebrate Mamoni's birthday as much as we were, if not more. The way Nourin and I were procrastinating about arranging everything, they were the people who saved us eventually. Thank you all for being so amazing. 
  Starting with the cake, the idea/ theme/ design came from two artistic people, Shirin and Anahita. Then that idea came into reality by another great artist, none other than Camy apu. Thanks to Mamoni's three of the favorite aunties for arranging the most beautiful themed cake that I have ever seen or eaten. 
About gifts, we don't even know the 'w' of wrapping gifts. Thanks to Robin, Shirin, Anahita, Limon vai for saving us again from buying gifts to wrapping those and for the game/ raffle draw ideas as well! 
Another important part was making the balloon garland and arranging other decorative things. Two of my amazing bros, Forhan and Nahin made the world's best garland that I have ever seen 
. Thanks so much, guys. It was really hard. But the good thing is we're now at ultra pro max level in making balloon garlands. Good for the future. Cheers!
